	<main>
		<img width="2500" height="1201" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="Maori ceremony" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-maori-language-and-place-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">The people of the Ngāti Tarāwhai tribe welcome participants to the inaugural <em>kura reo taiao</em>, or ‘language school of the natural world.’ They are gathered in front of Tarāwhai, a traditional wooden Māori meeting house on the North Island of Aotearoa New Zealand. Photo by Rawhitiroa Photography</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">To Speak the Language of the Land</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">Māori people are reclaiming their native language, even in the face of growing threats to the natural world on which it depends.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						Text by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/nic-low/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Nic Low</a>								<br/>
							Photos by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/te-rawhitiroa-bosch/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Te Rawhitiroa Bosch</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						December 12, 2024 | 4,600 words, about 23 minutes
					</aside>

					
